<recipe>
<title>
Cinnamon Bun Popcorn Recipe
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: I Heart Eating
PREP TIME: 5 minutes
COOK TIME: 55 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 1 hour
COURSE: Snack
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: popcorn
SERVINGS: 15 servings
</details>
<ingredients>
1/2 cup butter
1/2 cup brown sugar packed
1/2 cup granulated sugar
1/4 cup light corn syrup
1/2 teaspoon kosher salt
2 tablespoons ground cinnamon
1/4 teaspoon baking soda
1 teaspoon vanilla
1 cup marshmallows
10 cups popped popcorn
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 250 F. Line a large rimmed cookie sheet with a silicone baking mat.
In a large, heavy pot, melt butter.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup, and salt.
Stir, and continue cooking over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Once at a boil, stop stirring, and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, and cinnamon, baking soda, vanilla, and marshmallows.
Place popcorn on cookie sheet.
Pour cinnamon mixture over popcorn.
Bake for 15 minutes, and stir.
Continue baking 15 additional minutes. Stir.
Bake for 5-10 more minutes.
Stir one more time.
Let cool on baking sheet.
</instructions>
</recipe>
